## 4. Critical Math Rules

- **Never** use native JS floating-point arithmetic on currency values
- All inputs must be scaled to integers immediately: `Math.round(value * 10000)`
- All calculations performed on scaled integers only
- Results divided back to float only at final display formatting step
- Use `Number.EPSILON` in rounding: `Math.round((value + Number.EPSILON) * 100) / 100`
- **Never** use `toFixed()` for calculation logic — only for display formatting
- Quebec QST (9.975%) is calculated directly on the net consideration base — it does **not** compound on top of GST
- All provincial rates sourced exclusively from `src/data/taxRates.js` — never hardcoded elsewhere

### Mandatory Test Cases (must always pass)
| Input | Province | Expected Net | Expected Tax |
|---|---|---|---|
| $113.00 | Ontario (HST 13%) | $100.00 | $13.00 |
| $114.98 | Quebec (GST+QST) | $100.00 | $14.98 |
| $114.98 | Quebec French format | `100,00 $` | — |
| $100.00 | Ontario Auditor Mode | — | `$11.5044` |

