## 8. Localization Rules

- Quebec (QC) selected → all currency outputs use `toLocaleString('fr-CA')` with trailing `$` symbol → `100,00 $`
- All other provinces → `toLocaleString('en-CA')` with leading `$` → `$100.00`
- Clipboard copy function must strip all formatting symbols — write only raw numeric string (e.g. `1250.50`)
- Negative values display in accounting parentheses: `($254.10)` not `-$254.10`

---

## 9. Legal & Disclaimer Rules

The following disclaimer **must appear adjacent to every calculate button** on every page with a calculator:

> *"Calculations are arithmetic estimations only and do not constitute formal tax or corporate auditing advice. All figures must be verified against current CRA guidelines before filing."*

- Never label output as "tax advice"
- Never use "guaranteed accurate"
- Disclaimer placement: directly below calculate button, nowhere else

---

## 10. Accessibility Rules

- All inputs must have visible `<label>` elements with matching `for` and `id` attributes
- `aria-invalid` set on inputs with errors
- Error messages in `<span>` with `id` referenced by `aria-describedby`
- Focus rings never removed — only restyled
- WCAG AA contrast minimum in both dark and light modes
- Results section must include `aria-live="polite"` so screen readers announce updates
- Toggle switches require `aria-checked` and `role="switch"`
- All interactive elements must be keyboard navigable
- Minimum touch target height: 44px
- Color is never the only state indicator — always paired with text or iconography

---

## 11. Tooltip Rules

- Pure CSS only using `data-tooltip` attribute and `::after` pseudo-element — no JS libraries
- Visible on `:hover` and `:focus` states
- Width: 220px max
- Background: `#1e293b`, text: `#ffffff`
- Trigger uses `cursor: help`

### Tooltip Copy (exact wording)
- **Total Paid:** "The complete monetary value from your receipt or bank statement, inclusive of all combined sales taxes."
- **Base Cost:** "The absolute pre-tax cost of the goods or services. This is the value logged into corporate expense accounts before consumption taxes are applied."
- **Tax Removed:** "The isolated consumption tax extracted from your transaction. For CRA-registered entities, this amount is logged as an Input Tax Credit (ITC) to reduce net tax liabilities."
- **Quebec QST:** "Since January 1, 2013, QST is calculated directly on the net consideration base at 9.975% — it does not compound on top of GST."

