## 14. Testing

**Framework:** Vitest (unit), Playwright (E2E)

```bash
npx vitest run          # unit tests
npx playwright test     # E2E + link checker
```

- `calculateReverseTax()` must be exported from `app.js` for unit testing
- No code change is complete until all 4 mandatory test cases pass
- Playwright link checker pings all outbound `href^="http"` anchors and fails on non-200

---

## 15. GitHub Actions Cron

- Runs daily at `04:00 UTC`
- Runs Vitest and Playwright test suites only — **does not scrape external websites**
- All action references pinned to full SHA hashes — never `@v4` floating tags
- `GITHUB_TOKEN` permissions scoped to `contents: read` only
- Discord webhook URL stored as GitHub secret `DISCORD_TAX_ALERTS_WEBHOOK` — never hardcoded
- Use `npm ci` in all automated environments — never `npm install`

---

## 16. Cloudflare & Deployment Rules

- Build config: Static HTML / Vanilla JS — build command field **left empty**
- Cloudflare Bot Fight Mode must be enabled
- Cloudflare WAF free tier rules must be enabled
- CSP headers in `public/_headers` — single source of truth
- AdSense domain `googlesyndication.com` added to CSP **only when AdSense is actively used**

